               <p>WILLIAM READ. I am a <rs id="t18310217-251-viclabel1469" type="occupation">wheelwright</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-251-victim2291 t18310217-251-viclabel1469"></join>, and live in Princes-street, Lisson-grove, I lost this copper from a shed at the wharf - I cannot exactly say when; my apprentice first missed it.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Did he not say he missed it on the 8th? A. No - he mentioned no day.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-251-person2292">
                  RICHARD 
                  STRATTEN
               <interp inst="t18310217-251-person2292" type="surname" value="STRATTEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-251-person2292" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-251-person2292" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am apprentice to the prosecutor. The copper was safe at the wharf on the 31st of January - I missed it on the 3rd of February, and found it at Nash's on the 14th.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Did you ever say you missed it on the 8th? A. No.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-251-person2293">
                  JOSEPH 
                  NASH
               <interp inst="t18310217-251-person2293" type="surname" value="NASH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-251-person2293" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-251-person2293" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a broker, and dealer in rags and copper. I bought this copper of Mr. Boxall, for 12s. 6d. - Webster came and had it from me: when Read came he had a doubt of it, and I took him to Boxall.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. He had his doubts? A. Yes - he said he could not swear to it himself, but would find a man who could; he said there were three letters on it -Webster cleaned it, but could not find them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-251-person2294">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BOXALL
               <interp inst="t18310217-251-person2294" type="surname" value="BOXALL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-251-person2294" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-251-person2294" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I sold this copper to Nash for 12s. 6d. - I am a rag-merchant, and sometimes deal in stores; my landlord Arbour brought it to me to sell for him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-251-person2295">
                  THOMAS 
                  ARBOUR
               <interp inst="t18310217-251-person2295" type="surname" value="ARBOUR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-251-person2295" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-251-person2295" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a carpenter. I bought this copper from the prisoner, who was a tenant of mine, on the 5th of February - I set 9s. off his rent for it; he said it was his own - I did not ask where it came from.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Was any body present when he sold it to you? A. Yes, his wife - he told me he had it from a man who owed him money.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM READ. I cannot swear to this copper.</p>
